modules.description: Stores and manages input phrases during toplevel sessions using a buffer, executes the interactive read-eval-print loop, and locates initialization files for the OCaml toplevel. Works with string lists and a global buffer to handle session state and configuration. Used to customize and control the behavior of the OCaml interactive interpreter.

This module provides primitives for building interactive OCaml environments, including functions to evaluate code snippets, display file excerpts with context, and manage toplevel session state. It works directly with strings, string lists, and a custom value type representing toplevel bindings, using a global buffer to track input history. Concrete use cases include implementing custom REPLs, embedding interactive evaluation in tools, and extending the OCaml toplevel with file navigation and result display features.

This module manipulates OCaml abstract syntax trees to support interactive evaluation features, primarily handling variable bindings, module paths, and expression transformations. It provides utilities to extract and build variable names, construct module identifiers, and traverse or modify AST nodes within a structured environment tracking module contexts and bindings. Concrete use cases include rewriting expressions for REPL-like interactions and managing lexical scopes during AST transformations.
